{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce measures to address longevity and repair of products",
        "additional_details": "I think it will help tackle 'planned obsolescence', the practice of designing products to become obsolete or non-functional after a certain period, which in my view often leads to higher consumer spending and environmental waste.\r\n \r\nI would like to see measures to encourage durable, repairable products, promoting sustainable consumption, holding corporations to account for manufacturing practices.\r\n \r\nI think ending planned obsolescence will promote a more eco-friendly and consumer-centric market.",
        "background": "Introduce measures addressing longevity and repair of products, including:\r\n \r\n- requiring companies to provide repair manuals and spare parts\r\n \r\n- requiring manufacturers to consider longevity in product design\r\n \r\n- encouraging companies to promote sustainable consumption",
